      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I'm not a doctor, but it's generally recommended to err on the side of caution when it comes to ankle injuries. The RICE method (Rest, Ice, Compression, and Elevation) can be helpful for mild ankle sprains, but if your ankle is severely swollen and you're experiencing severe pain, it's better to seek medical attention. A visit to an urgent care or orthopedic clinic might be a safer option than trying to self-treat. However, if you're no longer able to bear weight on it, it's still best to seek medical help.",
